    public class Sheet.Range
extends java.lang.Object
implements Range
    The range class is used to select a range of Cell instances from the current Sheet.

      • createNullCells

        private void createNullCells()
        Some values for the Cell instances in this Range might be null, because they are not initialised. This may cause problems when calculating sums, or setting colors and text enhancements. Thus, now it's about time to create these missing Cell objects.
